main event: A radar/visual object was observed approaching at a much higher altitude in sight.
interesting points: The object was observed for almost 30 minutes.
There was insufficient information about the object's color, elevation, and change of direction.
A message was received from a commercial aircraft pilot reporting a very bright object at a much higher altitude, moving towards the aircraft or standing still.
The commercial aircraft pilot reported the observation at 18:10Z on February 18, 1961.
The report was received by the Commander, Caribbean Sea Frontier (COMCARIBSEAFRON) and forwarded to various military commands.
witnesses: Radar and visual observation, commercial aircraft pilot
photographs: No photographs present in the document
